{
  "_doc": "Magic: The Gathering | Marvel Super Heroes (code MSH) — Universes Beyond set, released 2026-06-26. Source: https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-marvel-super-heroes . Lineup is Play Boosters + Collector Boosters (plus Jumpstart/Commander products we don't model as packs) — no Draft Boosters, hence authoritative:true. Percentages are taken verbatim from the article's odds tables, which give per-slot shares; the two per-PACK phrasings are converted to per-slot weights: scene commons '8.6% of boosters' -> 8.6/7 = 1.2 per common slot, source material '1 out of 24 Play Boosters' -> (100/24)/7 = 0.6 per common slot, scene uncommons '12%' -> 12/3 = 4 per uncommon slot. Filter mappings: scene cards -> 'scene_card' (promo_types:poster, the verified Scryfall tag on SPM's fully-catalogued scene murals; MSH previews already carry it); logo / panel / classic-comic frames -> 'showcase' stand-in until Scryfall finishes cataloguing the Booster Fun sheets at release (only ~10 of the variant prints are indexed during previews — re-bake msh after street date and the chase outcomes fill in automatically); Source Material -> exact: set MAR (Marvel Universe) + 'msh_source_material' (collector 41-100, the 60-card MSH-era sheet; 1-40 belong to SPM); city calm & chaos full-art basics -> 'full_art_basic' merged into one pool because Scryfall doesn't distinguish calm from chaos and both appear at identical rates, so aggregate odds are unchanged (their article rates are summed: 10+10 nonfoil, 2.5+2.5 foil in the Play land slot); regular basics -> 'non_full_art_basic' so the land slot's basic share can never pull a city land; MSC reprint vs new-to-Magic Jumpstart sub-splits are merged into single MSC outcomes at the combined rate (both halves live in the same Scryfall set, indistinguishable by filter); 'Welcome Deck mythic' folded into the MSC mythic share. Sub-percentages reported as 'less than 1%' are entered as 0.5; the 'extremely low quantity' textless cosmic-foil Mind Stone is 0.1, mirroring spm.json's Soul Stone convention. AUDIT 2026-07 (post-release re-bake): reconciled scene + serialized outcomes against the RELEASED set. MSH has exactly 3 scene cards, all MYTHIC (promo_types:poster — Doctor Doom, Namor, Captain America); the article lists scene PERCENTAGES in common/uncommon/rare slots because a scene card REPLACES a common/uncommon, but the card itself is a mythic insert. All scene_card outcomes therefore drop their rarity constraint (the poster filter targets the 3 real scenes). The Textless Cosmic Foil Mind Stone (#385) is tagged promo_types:cosmicfoil (not serialized) → new cosmic_foil filter. Extended-art mythic outcomes now resolve (4 EA mythics printed).",
